The paper introduces a neural network architecture for solving constraint satisfaction problems, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The architecture involves training message passing networks, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses experiments and evaluations, which involve data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), as well as neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) for designing loss functions.
